02/03/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The European Commission (EC) confirmed on Monday (1 March) its decision to increase funding for Greece's agricultural development programmes.
The increase in funding will come under the Third Community Support Framework Programme for Greece, and is valued at 390m euros.
The confirmation was made at a meeting between Greek Agriculture Minister George Drys and a delegation of EC officials.
The delegation expressed satisfaction with the overall progress made by the ministry in implementing business programmes in the agriculture sector.
(ANA - 01/03/04)
